description:
Stanford University: Product Realization Lab

Monday, March 12

Our trip started off at Stanford University at its Product Realization Lab.

Homebase

We stayed in Foster City. One of the first things that we did when we arrived was eat at a diner called Heidi's Pies at 1 AM. (No, we did not try her pies.)

AutoDesk Museum

Wednesday, March 13

After getting some burgers, we decided to head down the street to the AutoDesk Museum. We spent a little under an hour there and saw 3D models, played with interactives, and almost got to use a 3D printer (ran out of time!).

Exploratiorium (After Dark)

Thursday, March 14

Do you ever just want to touch everything when you're in a museum? That was us at the Exploratorium, courtesy of Kristof. Tons and tons of things to do, to see, to interact with, all ranging from social experiments to biology to hardware.
